         <div type="translation" xml:lang="eng" resp="part:emfr">
       <p>Twelfth year of Īśvaravarman <supplied reason="explanation">Īccuvaraparumaṉ</supplied>.</p>
<p><supplied reason="subaudible">During</supplied> a fight/battle <supplied reason="subaudible">with</supplied> the Bāṇa king <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vāṇarācar</foreign></supplied> Kārōniri (or: Kārōṉiri),  the Bāṇa king of Ciṟaiyūr fell.</p>
</div>
         <div type="commentary">
         	
         	<p>
         		Īśvaravarman <supplied reason="explanation">Īccuvaraparumaṉ</supplied> is most probably a Pallava king, as his name is prefixed with <foreign>kō-vicaiya-</foreign>. He might be identified with Parameśvaravarman I or  Parameśvaravarman II. See Sarasvatam.<!--Update!-->
         	</p>
         	<p>See intro EC.<!--Update!--></p>
